library(pacman) ; p_load(tidyverse, dplyr, ggplot2, readr, tidyr, visdat, magrittr, tidymodels, keras, kernlab, brulee, ggthemes, tictoc)
setwd("/Users/joeandersen/desktop")
wtrpot <- read_csv("water_potability.csv")

SECTION 2: DATA CLEANING

#Checking missing values
vis_dat(wtrpot)

#Impute NA values with median value
wtrpot <- wtrpot %>%
  mutate(across(ph, ~replace_na(., median(., na.rm=TRUE)))) %>%
  mutate(across(Sulfate, ~replace_na(., median(., na.rm=TRUE)))) %>%
  mutate(across(Trihalomethanes, ~replace_na(., median(., na.rm=TRUE)))) 

#Setting seed
set.seed(007)

#Mutate binary classifier into categorical variable
wtrpot %<>% mutate(classifier = ifelse(Potability == 1, "Yes", "No"))

#Splitting dataset
wtrsplit = wtrpot %>% initial_split(prop = .8)
wtrtrain = wtrsplit %>% training()
wtrtest = wtrsplit %>% testing()

#visualize for missing values
vis_dat(wtrpot)

#setting up cross validation folds
folds = vfold_cv(wtrtrain, v = 5)

#null classifier
table(wtrtrain$classifier)
## 
##   No  Yes 
## 1603 1017

SECTION 3: TRAINING Model 1: Elastic Net

#defining model
elasticnet_model = linear_reg(mode = "regression", penalty = tune(), mixture = tune()) %>%
  set_engine("glmnet")

#defining preprocessing recipe
elasticnet_recipe = recipe(Potability ~ ., data = wtrtrain) %>%
  step_rm(contains("classifier")) %>%
    step_normalize(all_numeric_predictors())

#defining workflow
elasticnet_wf = workflow() %>%
  add_model(elasticnet_model) %>%
  add_recipe(elasticnet_recipe)

#tuning model for each combination of hyperparameters (penalty & mixture)
tic()
elasticnet_tune = elasticnet_wf %>% tune_grid(
  folds,
  grid = expand_grid(penalty = seq(0.1, 0.9, by = 0.05), mixture = seq(0.1, 0.9, by = 0.05)),
  metrics = metric_set(rmse))
toc()
## 24.584 sec elapsed

Model 2: Random Forest

#defining model
rf_model = rand_forest(mode = "classification", mtry = tune(), trees = tune(), min_n = tune()) %>%
  set_engine("ranger")

#defining preprocessing recipe
rf_recipe = recipe(classifier ~ ., data = wtrtrain) %>%
  step_rm(contains("Potability")) %>%
    step_normalize(all_numeric_predictors())

#defining workflow
rf_wf = workflow() %>%
  add_model(rf_model) %>%
  add_recipe(rf_recipe)

#defining penalty hyperparameter grid
rf_grid <- expand.grid(
  mtry = c(1, 2, 3, 5, 9),
  trees = c(50, 100, 250, 500, 1000),
  min_n = c(2, 4, 6, 10, 15, 25)
)

#tuning model for each combination of hyperparameters (mtry, trees, and min_n)
tic()
rf_tune = rf_wf %>% tune_grid(
  folds,
  grid = rf_grid,
  metrics = metric_set(roc_auc))
toc()
## 1247.608 sec elapsed

Model 3: Artificial Neural Network

#defining model
mlp_spec <- mlp(hidden_units = tune(), activation = tune(), mode = "classification") %>%
  set_engine("keras")

#defining preprocessing recipe
rec = recipe(classifier ~ ., wtrtrain) %>%
  step_rm(contains("Potability")) %>%
  step_normalize(all_predictors() & all_numeric())
  
#defining penalty hyperparameter grid
mlp_grid <- grid_regular(
  hidden_units(),
  activation(),
  levels = c(5, 4)
)

#defining workflow
mlp_wf = workflow() %>%
  add_recipe(rec) %>%
  add_model(mlp_spec)

#tuning model for each combination of hyperparameters (hidden units & activation function)
tic()
mlp_tune = mlp_wf %>% tune_grid(
    folds,
    grid = mlp_grid,
    control = control_grid(save_pred = TRUE))
toc()
## 238.909 sec elapsed

Model 4: Support Vector Machine

#defining model
svm_spec <- svm_rbf(mode = "classification", cost = tune(), margin = tune(), rbf_sigma = tune()) %>%
  set_engine("kernlab") 

#defining preprocessing recipe
rec = recipe(classifier ~ ., wtrtrain) %>%
  step_rm(contains("Potability")) %>%
  step_normalize(all_predictors() & all_numeric())
  
#defining hyperparameter grid
svm_grid <- expand.grid(
  cost = c(.1, 1, 10, 20),
  margin = c(.1, .5, 1),
  rbf_sigma = c(.01, .1, 1, 10)
)

#defining workflow
svm_wf = workflow() %>%
  add_recipe(rec) %>%
  add_model(svm_spec)
  
#tuning model for each combination of hyperparameters (cost, margin, radial basis function)
tic()
svm_tune = svm_wf %>% tune_grid(
    folds,
    grid = svm_grid,
    control = control_grid(save_pred = TRUE))
toc()
## 218.083 sec elapsed

Section 7: Comparing Predictive Power

#Factoring classifier
truth <- factor(wtrtest$Potability)

#Extracting Elastic Net ROC Curve
df_en <- data.frame(truth, Class1 = 0)
roc_en <- roc_curve(df_en, truth, Class1) #calculate ROC curve
## Warning: Returning more (or less) than 1 row per `summarise()` group was deprecated in
## dplyr 1.1.0.
##  Please use `reframe()` instead.
##  When switching from `summarise()` to `reframe()`, remember that `reframe()`
##   always returns an ungrouped data frame and adjust accordingly.
##  The deprecated feature was likely used in the yardstick package.
##   Please report the issue at <]8;;https://github.com/tidymodels/yardstick/issueshttps://github.com/tidymodels/yardstick/issues]8;;>.
autoplot(roc_en)

#Extracting Random Forest ROC Curve
best_rf = rf_wf %>% finalize_workflow(select_best(rf_tune, metric = "roc_auc")) #extract best model
best_rf_fit = best_rf %>% fit(wtrtrain) #fit model on all training data
best_rf_predict = best_rf_fit %>% predict(wtrtest, type = "prob") #predict 
estimate_rf = best_rf_predict$.pred_No

df_rf <- data.frame(truth, Class1 = estimate_rf)
roc_rf <- roc_curve(df_rf, truth, Class1) #calculate ROC curve
autoplot(roc_rf)

#Extracting Neural Network ROC Curve
best_nn = mlp_wf %>% finalize_workflow(select_best(mlp_tune, metric = "roc_auc")) #extract best model
best_nn_fit = best_nn %>% fit(wtrtrain) #fit model on all training data
best_nn_predict = best_nn_fit %>% predict(wtrtest, type = "prob") #predict 
estimate_nn = best_nn_predict$.pred_No

df_nn <- data.frame(truth, Class1 = estimate_nn)
roc_nn <- roc_curve(df_nn, truth, Class1) #calculate ROC curve
autoplot(roc_nn)

#Extracting Support Vector Machine ROC Curve
best_svm = svm_wf %>% finalize_workflow(select_best(svm_tune, metric = "roc_auc")) #extract best model
best_svm_fit = best_svm %>% fit(wtrtrain) #fit model on all training data
best_svm_predict = best_svm_fit %>% predict(wtrtest, type = "prob") #predict 
estimate_svm = best_svm_predict$.pred_No

df_svm <- data.frame(truth, Class1 = estimate_svm)
roc_svm <- roc_curve(df_svm, truth, Class1) #calculate ROC curve
autoplot(roc_svm)

#Graphing all models together
roc_data <- rbind(
  data.frame(model = "Elastic Net", roc_en), 
  data.frame(model = "Random Forest", roc_rf),
  data.frame(model = "Neural Network", roc_nn),
  data.frame(model = "Support Vector Machine", roc_svm)
)
table(roc_data$model)
## 
##            Elastic Net         Neural Network          Random Forest 
##                      3                    658                    658 
## Support Vector Machine

# Plot ROC curves on a single graph
ggplot(roc_data, aes(x = 1 - specificity, y = sensitivity, color = model)) +
  geom_line() +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("red", "blue", "green", "orange")) +
  labs(x = "False Positive Rate", y = "True Positive Rate", 
       color = "Model") +
  ggtitle("ROC Curves for Models")
